Hey,

Fraser stayed over last night, was a barrel-o-laughs, we played guitar a bit and just generally mucked about like the cool gents we are.
Did fuck all today, fraser left about 16:30, I never really bothered to get showered or anything.
Listening to The Misfits for the first time in ages, dont know why.  So much <small><strike>randomness</strike></small>.
Anyway thats all for now, Not looking forward to going back to school on wednesday AT ALL.
Ah well, I suppose I should be greatful I have no homework, and that its not a monday.
But Im not, so Ha.

Well, thats all for now.

Goodbye.

Hello.
Well yesterday was interesting.  I went to meet Max at kelvingrove park which took ages as I completely forgot the way, we then went up for Roisin, and then walked up to some shop on Dunbarton Road and bought vodka, and then we met <strike>Coleenxcore</strike> and bought robinsons to mix the vodka with, how hardcore are we?  We then sat and consumed it in the Botanical Gardens, it, as per usual (or so im told) went straight to coleens head, and it was funny watching her struggle to walk, we went to some cafe so they could go to the toilet, and had a conversation with the chef, or deliveryman who was also there, before walking up to kelvingrove again to sit about, we bumped in to some people who were skating, who Roisin and Coleen knew ( ? ) but then we bumped into Andy Clark, who is a complete dick, thinks hes so hard.
We then wandered about again, and Max had to go home, so we sat about for a while, then headed back up to Great Western Road, where we bumped into 3 bams, who kind of mugged me for 2 pounds lol (obviously scaffs).
Then I decided to go home.
More probably happened but I was slightly drunk so dont remember some of it.

Thats all for now
Laters

James

<font color=#E8C12D><u>14 Hours Ahead</u></font> - A head that's heavier than lead and I've got toothpicks in my eyes.
A smile more yellow than the sky.
I've got a song stuck in my head.
One that I miss more than my bed.
It's a song sung from a fallen milkman who's drinking bleach instead.
I'm much like him.
<font color=#E8C12D><u>14 Hours Unfed</u></font> - I spent the last cents in my head.
They're worth much less than pennies now.
Food for one thought shared with a crowd.
And I've got a painting in my head.
A deeper blue bled thicker red.
More Red than Bloody Marys coast to coast.
I hate flying I said - That's what I said.
<font color=#E8C12D><u>Sad Sorry Excuse</u></font>
Just like everything that made her smile and everything I use.
I won't go back to the way it was.
<strike>I'm now huffing gas and sniffing paint to take away this buzz that I call you</strike>
